Count 1.
FILED.

Defendant Donovan Dewayne Austin in court with attorney Mark Allan Dluzak.  Defendant Donovan Dewayne Austin in custody.  
Dennis Patrick Murphy appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Amended Information filed.  Defense counsel acknowledged receipt of a copy of the Amended Information, waived its reading.  

Charge amended to COUNT 1: POSSESSION OF THC, (TETRAHYDROCANNABINOLS)- 2ND AND SUBSEQUENT OFFENSE, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 961.41(3g)(e), 939.50(3)(i),  a Class I Felony

Defendant prepared to enter change of plea.  Hearing proceeded.  Negotiations set forth by the state.

COUNT 1:  The defendant was advised of his constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum to Plea Questionnaire, and Elements sheet received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction. 

Sentencing proceeds.   Statements by the state, defense, and defendant. 

COURT ADVISES the defendant he cannot own/possess any firearms, he must provide a DNA sample, and cannot vote until his civil rights are restored.  

COURT ORDERS defendant to serve a term in the Wisconsin State Prison system - TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE - 42 MONTHS with 0 days credit -  INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT -  18 MONTHS -  EXTENDED SUPERVISION - 24 MONTHS.  This sentence is CONSECUTIVE TO COUNT 1 OF 13CF3360, CONCURRENT TO COUNT 2 OF 13CF3360.

COURT ORDERS defendant to all mandatory costs, assessments and surcharges by the end of the sentence or a civil judgment is to be entered against the defendant and subject to other collection.  

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  1) no violations of criminal law rising to the level of probable cause; 2) pay any monetary amounts ordered but not paid while in the institution; 3) AODA, programs or treatment as recommended; 4) no illegally controlled substances; 5) random screening; 6) seek and maintain employment.

Court finds defendant IS NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Substance Abuse Program.

COURT ORDERS:
-  defendant to provide a biological specimen for DNA analysis;
-  DOC to collect monetary sums/amounts at a maximum rate of 25% of prison funds.

Appeal rights given.  Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence (copy to defendant), Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief and Ineligible Voting Notice and Acknowledgment received and filed.  Copies given to the defendant.
